---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Hanafi Firman — solution architect working on systems design and AI engineering."
>
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-16 animate-rise">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-soft mb-4">
        About
      </p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
        Hi, I'm Hanafi.
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-editorial">
      <p>
        I'm a solution architect. Most of my work sits between product teams who
        know <em>what</em> they want to build and engineering teams who know
        <em>how</em> to build it — my job is to shape the
        <em>shape</em> of the thing so both sides can move.
      </p>

      <p>
        On a typical week, I'm scoping out solution designs, reviewing technical
        approaches with senior engineers, and running proof-of-concepts for
        things we're thinking of adopting — lately a lot of that has been
        around AI tooling for software engineering workflows.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this site</h2>

      <p>
        I've been doing this long enough to notice the same trade-offs
        reappear in different disguises. Writing them down helps me think, and
        hopefully helps someone else avoid a dead-end I've already walked into.
      </p>

      <p>
        The topics I keep coming back to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Architecture & design patterns</strong> — how to scope
          solutions that survive contact with real teams and real deadlines.</li>
        <li><strong>AI for software engineering</strong> — what actually works,
          what's overhyped, and what's changing faster than anyone can keep up
          with.</li>
        <li><strong>Engineering leadership</strong> — the soft parts of the job
          that don't fit in an architecture diagram but determine whether the
          diagram gets built.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>

      <p>
        I'm open to conversations about architecture consulting, AI engineering
        experiments, or just comparing notes. Best ways to reach me:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><a href={SITE.social.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a> — for anything work-related</li>
        <li><a href={SITE.social.github}>GitHub</a> — for code and side projects</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
